The '''2007 Thailand Open''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Tennis court#Indoor courts|indoor hard courts]]. It was the 5th edition of the [[PTT Thailand Open (ATP)|Thailand Open]], and was part of the [[ATP International Series|International Series]] of the [[2007 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Impact, Muang Thong Thani|Impact Arena]] in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]], from September 24 through September 30, 2007.

The singles field featured [[Association of Tennis Professionals|ATP]] No. 3, [[2007 French Open – Men's Singles#Finals|French Open]] and [[2007 Wimbledon Championships – Men's Singles#Finals|Wimbledon semifinalist]], [[2007 U.S. Open (tennis)|US Open]] runner-up, [[2007 Next Generation Adelaide International|Adelaide]], [[2007 Estoril Open|Estoril]], [[2007 Miami Masters|Miami Masters]] and [[2007 Canada Masters|Canada Masters]] champion [[Novak Djokovic]], [[2007 Australian Open – Men's Singles#Finals|Australian Open semifinalist]], [[2007 Queen's Club Championships|Queen's Club]] and [[2007 Legg Mason Tennis Classic|Washington]] titlist [[Andy Roddick]], and [[2007 Gerry Weber Open|Halle]] winner [[Tomáš Berdych]]. Also lined up were [[2007 Regions Morgan Keegan Championships and the Cellular South Cup|Memphis]] champion [[Tommy Haas]], [[2007 Croatia Open Umag|Umag]] winner [[Carlos Moyá]], [[Dmitry Tursunov]], [[Ivo Karlović]] and [[Fernando Verdasco]].

==Champions==
===Singles===
{{main|2007 Thailand Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|RUS}} '''[[Dmitry Tursunov]]''' def. {{flagicon|GER}} [[Benjamin Becker]], 6–2, 6–1
*It was Dmitry Tursunov's 2nd title of the year, and his 3rd overall.

===Doubles===
{{main|2007 Thailand Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|THA}} '''[[Sanchai Ratiwatana]]''' / {{flagicon|THA}} '''[[Sonchat Ratiwatana]]''' def. {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Michaël Llodra]] / {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Nicolas Mahut]], 3–6, 7–5, [10–7]

