{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Ajman International Cricket Stadium | nickname = Ajman Oval | full name = Ajman Oval | image = | caption = | country = United Arab Emirates | location = [[Emirates City]], [[Ajman]], [[United Arab Emirates]] | operator = Privately Owned | tenants = [[United Arab Emirates national cricket team]] | establishment = 2014 | seating_capacity = n/a | end1 = City End, | end2 = Pavilion End | club1 = [[Ajman cricket team]] | year1 = 2014-present | date = August 12, | year = 2015 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/27/12595.html Ground profile }} The '''Ajman Oval''' is a cricket ground in [[Ajman]], [[UAE]]. Oval provides state-of-the-art facilities outdoor pitches, complemented by the latest technology to allow coaches to assess all areas of a player’s game.<ref>[http://www.emirates247.com/sports/local/pakistan-cricketers-inaugurate-new-ajman-oval-2014-11-29-1.571600 Pakistan cricketers inaugurate new Ajman Oval]</ref><ref>[http://sport360.com/tags/ajman-oval Sports 360]</ref>
The ground is privately owned and first of its kind in the northern region. It was the first turf ground in ajman with approval from the [[Ajman Cricket Council]] and has four turf wickets, a lush green outfield with the pavilion designed to give it the Arabian style structure. Besides this, there is an international standard dressing rooms and dugouts, large side screens, floodlights, digital scoreboards, a mosque, several mounts with barbecue areas and number of palm and neem trees have been planted for beautification of stadium. The stadium also has a cricket academy, coffee and sports shop well as good parking space.<ref>[http://gulfnews.com/sport/uae/cricket/ajman-oval-changing-the-shape-of-uae-cricket-1.1564921 Gulf News]</ref><ref>[https://en-maktoob.news.yahoo.com/flood-lit-ajman-oval-cricket-ground-inaugurated-065554046.html Yahoo cricket]</ref>
Currently, the stadium has hosted various local tournament like Age Steel Ramadan T-20 Cup and FS T20 Premier League but [[Ajman Cricket Council]] hoping to-get international cricket to city.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/27/12595_misc.html Other matches played]</ref>
