{{more citations needed|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox football club |clubname = Governors Athletic F.C. |image = GovernorsAthletic.png |image_size = 130px |fullname = Governors Athletic Football Club |nickname = The Governors |founded = 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.govenorsathletic.co.uk/club/292625/History|title=History|publisher=Governors Athletic F.C.|accessdate=12 December 2014|archiveurl=//web.archive.org/web/20160304002600/http://www.govenorsathletic.co.uk/club/292625/History|archivedate=4 March 2016}}</ref> |ground = Bemahague School 3G Pitch |capacity = |chairman = |1st Team Manager = Karlos Bandero |Combination Manager = Matthew 'Molesworth |Groundsman = Lazy fella |league = [[Isle of Man Football League]] [[Isle of Man Football League#Division Two|Division Two]] |season = [[2016–17 Isle of Man League|2016–17]] |position = Division Two, 11/13 |pattern_la1 = |pattern_b1 = _chevron_black |pattern_ra1 = |pattern_sh1 = |pattern_so1 = |leftarm1 = 000000 |body1 = 00FF00 |rightarm1 = 000000 |shorts1 = 00FF00 |socks1 = 000000 }} '''Governors Athletic F.C.''' are a [[Association football|football]] club from the [[Isle of Man]]. They compete in the [[Isle of Man Football League]].
Governors Athletic were founded in 2014, and for their first season played their home matches at Nobles Park in Douglas. For the 2015–16 Season, Governors Athletic secured the new 3G pitch at Bemahague and played first official league game there on 15 August 2015.
The first team achieved its first victory on 10 September 2016, with a 1–0 victory against Michael United. A 94th-minute goal from Andrew Zola Ronan sealed the win.
