{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Islecroft Stadium | nickname = | image = Islecroft Stadium.jpg | size = 300px | caption = | fullname = | location = [[Dalbeattie]], [[Scotland]] | pushpin_map = Scotland Dumfries and Galloway | pushpin_mapsize = 250 | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Dumfries and Galloway | pushpin_label_position = left | coordinates = {{coord|54|56|5.96|N|3|49|2.8|W|type:landmark|display=inline}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1950 | surface = Grass<ref name="Soccerway_Islecroft">[https://int.soccerway.com/teams/scotland/dalbeattie-star-fc/5011/venue/ Islecroft Stadium], ''soccerway.com''. Retrieved 10 August 2013.</ref> | tenants = [[Dalbeattie Star F.C.]] | seating_capacity = 1,320 (100 seated) | dimensions = }} '''Islecroft Stadium''' is a football stadium located in the town of [[Dalbeattie]] in [[Scotland]]. The stadium was opened in 1950 and is the home of [[Scottish Lowland Football League]] club [[Dalbeattie Star F.C.|Dalbeattie Star]].<ref name="WS_Islecroft">[http://www.worldstadia.com/stadium/scotland/islecroft_stadium/15233.php Details for Islecroft Stadium, Dalbeattie], ''worldstadia.com''. Retrieved 10 August 2013.</ref> It has a capacity of 1,320 with 100 seats.<ref name="NLS_Dalbeattie">[http://nonleaguescotland.org.uk/dalbeattie.htm Dalbeattie Star], ''nonleaguescotland.org.uk''. Retrieved 10 August 2013.</ref>
