{{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Ju-Jitsu Federation of the Philippines |logo= |size= |sport= [[Ju-Jitsu]] |abbrev= JFP |founded= 2015 |recognized= 2015 |association= JJFF, PSC, POC |headquarters= |president = Ramon "Choy" Cojuangco |chairman = |vicepresident = Jason Lima |secretary = Ferdie Agustin |website= [http://www.bjjfp.com Official website] |prevfounded = |countryflag= Philippines |code= PHI }}
'''Ju-Jitsu Federation of the Philippines''' (abbreviated as JFP) is the [[Sports governing body|national sports association]] (NSA) for [[Jujitsu]] in the [[Philippines]]. It was formed in 2015 and represented by 50 jujitsu clubs in the country.<ref name=balita1>{{cite web|url= http://balita.net.ph/2015/12/26/poc-tinanggap-ang-jiu-jitsu-federation/|title=POC, tinanggap ang Jiu-Jitsu Federation (POC accepts Jiu-Jitsu Federation)|publisher=Balita|date=26 December 2015|accessdate=2 January 2016|language=Filipino, English}}</ref> Currently, JFP is recognized by the [[International Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Federation]], the [[Sport Jiu Jitsu International Federation]] (SJJIF), the [[Philippine Sports Commission]] (PSC) and the [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] (POC).{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
It was admitted as the 50th regular member of the [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] in November 2015.<ref name=newestpocmember>{{cite web|url=http://sports.inquirer.net/202469/jujitsu-group-is-newest-poc-member|title=Jujitsu group is newest POC member|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=31 December 2015|accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=balita1/> ==References== {{reflist}}
