{{italic title}} '''''Nemzeti Sport''''' (the title means "National Sport") is a Hungarian sports daily.<ref>{{cite web|title=Media and Communications: Hungary|publisher=''[[Library of Congress]]''|url=https://www.loc.gov/rr/international/european/hungary/resources/hu-media.html|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hungary to host World Cup champion Italy in soccer friendly|publisher=''[[International Herald Tribune]]''|url=http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2007/08/21/sports/EU-SPT-SOC-Hungary-Italy.php|date=21 August 2007|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''Nemzeti Sport'' was founded in 1903.<ref>{{cite web|title=The press in Hungary|work=BBC News|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/3616011.stm|date=29 April 2004|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref> The paper is owned by [[Ringier]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Country Report - Hungary (2004)|work=[[Freedom House]]|url=http://www.freedomhouse.org/template.cfm?page=47&nit=334&year=2004|year=2004|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref> of [[Switzerland]]. It is frequently cited by quality English-language media<ref>{{cite web|title=Gera puts promotion before cup|work=Sky Sports|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,13864_3385100,00.html|date=4 March 2008|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Soccer-Hungary Golden Team keeper Grosics has lung operation|work=Reuters|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/UK_WORLDFOOTBALL/idUKL2656547020080126|date=26 January 2008|accessdate=11 May 2008}}</ref> The paper is published in [[broadsheet]] format.<ref name=wan3/>
Its publisher claimed that the newspaper had the third largest circulation in the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hungary|publisher=Ringier|url=http://www.ringier.com/index.cfm?rub=187|accessdate=11 May 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070713224503/http://www.ringier.com/index.cfm?rub=187|archivedate=13 July 2007|df=}}</ref> The circulation of the paper was 96,000 copies in 2003.<ref name=wan3>{{cite web|title=World Press Trends|url=http://www.wan-press.org/ecrire/upload/wpt2004.pdf|publisher=World Association of Newspapers|accessdate=15 February 2015|location=Paris|date=2004}}</ref> It had a circulation of 95,111 copies in 2009, making it the fourth most read daily in the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Communicating Europe: Hungary Manual|url=http://www.esiweb.org/pdf/enlargement_debates_manual_hungary.pdf|publisher=European Stability Initiative|accessdate=26 November 2014|date=December 2010}}</ref>
==Genre== Although Nemzeti Sport is considered as one of the most reliable source of information on sport, recently the online version of the paper became increasingly [[Sensationalism|sensational]]. An example of this tendency can be observed by the news items about the possible transfer of the [[Hungary national football team]] and [[Dinamo Moscow]] left-winger [[Balázs Dzsudzsák]].
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Date !! Team |- | 28/07/2015 || [[Hertha BSC]] and [[Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/legiosok/dinamo-a-hertha-mellett-a-serie-a-is-realis-opcio-dzsudzsaknak-2428889|title=Dinamo: a Hertha mellett a Serie A is reális opció Dzsudzsáknak|date=28 July 2015|publisher=Nemzeti Sport}}</ref> |- | 12/07/2015 || [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/legiosok/legiosok-kozel-a-megallapodas-dzsudzsak-uj-klubjaval-sajtohir-2425637|title=Légiósok: közel a megállapodás Dzsudzsák új klubjával – sajtóhír|date=12 July 2015|publisher=Nemzeti Sport}}</ref> |- | 27/05/2015 || [[Internazionale Milano|Internazionale]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/olasz_labdarugas/inter-mancininter-20-ket-biztos-erkezo-az-egyik-dzsudzsak-2415981|title=Inter: MancinInter 2.0 - a "biztos" érkezők között Dzsudzsák|date=27 May 2015|publisher=Nemzeti Sport}}</ref> |- |}
